nominal neutron flux intensity of TC-Pn is 5.86E+10
(n/cm2/sec) at 1 MW power operation. The AUTHORs
have confirmed that the TC-Pn was extremely
thermalized on the basis of Westcott`s convention in
another experiment. (See Fig. 8 in the REL-REF.)

The reaction rates of the Np-237 samples were
obtained from the yield of the 984.45-keV gamma rays
The thermal-neutron fluxes were derived using the
reaction rates and the thermal cross sections of the
monitors (Sc-45, Co-59, Mo-98, Ta-181 and Au-197).
Thermal capture cross sections and g-factors of
the monitors were taken from the REL-REF.
The cross section of Np-237 was derived from
the reaction rates and the activities of the samples,
Self-shielding coefficients for the monitors were
calculated from neutron capture cross-sections and
Those for the Np-237 samples were estimated to be
unity from its number of nuclei.
Thermal capture dross section of the monitors were
assumed to deduce the thermal neutron flux.
